WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:12.940 --> 00:00:14.670
Inherited will...

3
00:00:14.670 --> 00:00:17.580
the tides of time, and humanity's dreams...

4
00:00:17.580 --> 00:00:20.410
They cannot be stopped.

5
00:00:20.410 --> 00:00:23.520
As long as people seek freedom,

6
00:00:23.520 --> 00:00:26.150
these things will never cease to be.

7
00:00:34.860 --> 00:00:41.080
Mirai dake shinjiteru dareka ga warattemo kamawanai
I only believe in the future -- I don't care if anyone laughs

8
00:00:41.120 --> 00:00:46.600
Hashitteru jounetsu ga anata wo KIRA mekaseru
That racing passion makes you shine

9
00:00:46.620 --> 00:00:52.140
Mabushi sugi, demo mitsumete itai
It's too bright, but I want to gaze at it

10
00:00:52.480 --> 00:00:56.120
Dokka "bigaku" kanjiteru
I sense "aesthetics" somewhere

11
00:00:56.120 --> 00:00:58.160
I'm really really stuck on you

12
00:00:59.480 --> 00:01:02.740
Dare ni mo nitenai yume no senaka wo
I follow, follow in the footsteps

13
00:01:02.740 --> 00:01:06.030
Oikakete oikaketeku
of a dream that resembles no one

14
00:01:06.030 --> 00:01:09.260
DORAMATIKKU te ni ireru made
Until I dramatically get it

15
00:01:09.280 --> 00:01:15.080
Believe in Wonderland!

16
00:01:18.120 --> 00:01:21.160
Dare ni mo mienai yume no KATACHI wo
I'm going to catch, catch the shape

17
00:01:21.260 --> 00:01:24.240
Tsukamaete tsukamaeteku
of a dream no one can see

18
00:01:24.520 --> 00:01:30.260
Watashi wa tsuite yuku kara atsui KIMOCHI
I'm going to go with you, so passionate feelings

19
00:01:30.500 --> 00:01:33.620
TSUJITSUMA awase betsu ni iranai
I don't really need everything to add up

20
00:01:33.600 --> 00:01:36.790
Arifureta nichijou yori mo
Rather than run-of-the-mill daily life,

21
00:01:36.800 --> 00:01:40.390
PARADAISU mezashite hashire
run for paradise instead

22
00:01:40.390 --> 00:01:45.920
Believe in Wonderland!

23
00:01:51.720 --> 00:01:53.550
Rumble Ball!

24
00:01:56.680 --> 00:01:58.930
The rumble ball's effects
last three minutes.

25
00:01:58.970 --> 00:02:03.600
The Skies of Drum

26
00:01:59.430 --> 00:02:01.680
That's three minutes to take you down!

27
00:02:01.680 --> 00:02:03.020
Three minutes?!

28
00:02:03.560 --> 00:02:06.900
You have no chance of defeating me,
much less in three minutes!

29
00:02:07.190 --> 00:02:09.360
Three minutes? That's amazing!

30
00:02:09.650 --> 00:02:11.860
Three minutes? That's amazing!

31
00:02:14.240 --> 00:02:16.530
We're about to see
something interesting.

32
00:02:16.530 --> 00:02:20.290
Dammit! Let me fight, too!

33
00:02:20.290 --> 00:02:21.500
Rumble!

34
00:02:22.910 --> 00:02:23.870
What...

35
00:02:23.870 --> 00:02:26.250
did you say you could do?!

36
00:02:29.670 --> 00:02:32.630
Marimo's Snow-Melting Arrow!

37
00:02:34.260 --> 00:02:36.680
Walk Point: Limb Boost!

38
00:02:41.140 --> 00:02:43.690
A transformation?!
I was expecting more!

39
00:02:43.690 --> 00:02:46.400
In other words, you have
the powers of a devil fruit...

40
00:02:46.480 --> 00:02:48.770
a zoan, just like Dalton!

41
00:02:48.770 --> 00:02:50.780
A reindeer human, huh?!

42
00:02:50.780 --> 00:02:53.740
Heavy Point: Weight Boost!

43
00:02:54.360 --> 00:02:56.240
I'm a human reindeer!

44
00:02:56.240 --> 00:02:57.570
Same difference!

45
00:02:57.570 --> 00:03:02.160
I know everything about the three-point
transformation you zoans use.

46
00:03:02.520 --> 00:03:05.710
Marimo's Super Surprise
Quattro Hammer!

47
00:03:06.620 --> 00:03:09.750
I've seen all your forms.

48
00:03:09.750 --> 00:03:12.920
You use your powers
to fight, similar to Dalton.

49
00:03:12.920 --> 00:03:15.130
But there's no way those...

50
00:03:15.130 --> 00:03:18.590
Jumping Point: Jumping Boost!

51
00:03:18.590 --> 00:03:21.430
...can take me down!

52
00:03:25.390 --> 00:03:27.900
He jumped! Man, he can really jump!

53
00:03:27.900 --> 00:03:29.360
Whoa!

54
00:03:30.150 --> 00:03:31.400
What?!

55
00:03:31.400 --> 00:03:33.780
What's that form?!

56
00:03:34.320 --> 00:03:38.610
Wasn't his hybrid form the little reindeer
from earlier?! How impudent!

57
00:03:38.610 --> 00:03:41.660
Guard Point: Guard Boost!

58
00:03:52.210 --> 00:03:53.380
Another?!

59
00:03:57.720 --> 00:03:58.760
Impossible!

60
00:03:58.760 --> 00:04:00.470
I hit him dead on!

61
00:04:00.470 --> 00:04:02.050
It won't work!

62
00:04:02.430 --> 00:04:06.060
Zoans are only supposed
to have three forms!

63
00:04:06.060 --> 00:04:07.890
What the heck are you?

64
00:04:07.890 --> 00:04:12.820
The rumble ball is a drug that alters
the wavelength of devil fruit transformations.

65
00:04:12.820 --> 00:04:16.780
During my five years of research,
I found four more transformation points.

66
00:04:17.280 --> 00:04:19.740
A seven-point transformation?!

67
00:04:20.110 --> 00:04:21.200
A... seven...?

68
00:04:21.200 --> 00:04:23.660
Who cares how many
transformations you have?!

69
00:04:23.660 --> 00:04:24.410
A...?

70
00:04:25.160 --> 00:04:28.620
A seven-point transforming reindeer!

71
00:04:29.080 --> 00:04:31.000
What's his damage?

72
00:04:31.000 --> 00:04:34.630
After hearing "seven-point transformation,"
he's probably on cloud nine.

73
00:04:34.630 --> 00:04:36.130
You bastard...

74
00:04:36.130 --> 00:04:39.130
Have you forgotten about
your fight against me?

75
00:04:39.590 --> 00:04:42.930
I'm not going to fall
for such an obvious bluff!

76
00:04:42.930 --> 00:04:44.850
It's not a bluff!

77
00:04:50.900 --> 00:04:53.770
Arm Point: Arm Boost!

78
00:05:08.080 --> 00:05:09.410
Let me tell you something.

79
00:05:09.410 --> 00:05:13.380
My hooves are hard as iron!
They can even destroy boulders!

80
00:05:13.380 --> 00:05:14.970
Amazing!

81
00:05:16.130 --> 00:05:18.800
Don't underestimate me, you bastard!

82
00:05:19.970 --> 00:05:21.180
This'll show you!

83
00:05:21.180 --> 00:05:22.760
Marimo's Super Surprise...

84
00:05:24.430 --> 00:05:26.640
Quattro Axe:

85
00:05:27.350 --> 00:05:29.180
Snow-Splitting Blade!

86
00:05:35.110 --> 00:05:38.280
Hey... The castle wall is crumbling!

87
00:05:39.940 --> 00:05:42.070
Tch! He dodged it!

88
00:05:42.700 --> 00:05:44.740
Then, how about...

89
00:05:44.740 --> 00:05:46.030
this?!

90
00:05:46.700 --> 00:05:49.120
Omnidirectional Snow Splitter!

91
00:05:55.290 --> 00:05:57.040
Where'd that optimism go?!

92
00:05:57.040 --> 00:05:59.880
You can't win if you just
keep dodging, you know!

93
00:06:08.560 --> 00:06:10.560
Brain Point: Brain Boost!

94
00:06:12.180 --> 00:06:14.310
I wasn't just dodging.

95
00:06:16.230 --> 00:06:18.360
I was searching for your weak point.

96
00:06:18.360 --> 00:06:19.190
What?!

97
00:06:19.190 --> 00:06:20.690
This will finish you.

98
00:06:20.690 --> 00:06:21.690
Scope!

99
00:06:29.490 --> 00:06:32.120
A... A beam! He's
gonna shoot a beam!

100
00:06:32.120 --> 00:06:33.870
As if, you moron!

101
00:06:33.870 --> 00:06:35.040
Shut up!

102
00:06:35.540 --> 00:06:36.710
It's definitely a beam!

103
00:06:36.710 --> 00:06:38.210
I don't care what anyone says, it's a beam!

104
00:06:38.210 --> 00:06:40.380
I don't care what anyone says, it's a beam!
How can you know that, huh?!

105
00:06:40.380 --> 00:06:41.510
I just know! It's a beam! A beam!
How can you know that, huh?!

106
00:06:41.510 --> 00:06:42.720
I just know! It's a beam! A beam!
Then what kind of beam?!

107
00:06:42.720 --> 00:06:44.050
Now's my chance...
Then what kind of beam?!

108
00:06:44.430 --> 00:06:47.510
You were searching for
my weak point?! So what?!

109
00:06:55.440 --> 00:06:57.770
I don't have a weak point!

110
00:06:57.770 --> 00:06:59.860
All you can do
is transform and dodge!

111
00:06:59.860 --> 00:07:02.360
If anyone's finished, it's you!

112
00:07:05.740 --> 00:07:06.360
Found it!

113
00:07:08.120 --> 00:07:09.080
His jaw!

114
00:07:24.220 --> 00:07:25.470
Where'd he go?!

115
00:07:28.090 --> 00:07:29.180
Cloven...

116
00:07:38.150 --> 00:07:40.940
Roseo!

117
00:07:54.910 --> 00:07:56.250
Three minutes.

118
00:07:56.750 --> 00:07:59.630
Way to go, reindeer!

119
00:07:59.630 --> 00:08:01.210
Hey, Luffy!

120
00:08:01.960 --> 00:08:02.880
Where is that guy?

121
00:08:02.880 --> 00:08:04.010
Which guy?

122
00:08:04.010 --> 00:08:06.260
That tin bastard! He's gone!

123
00:08:10.930 --> 00:08:15.640
He came up on his woolly hippo,
so he wouldn't go down on his own.

124
00:08:15.640 --> 00:08:17.850
When the hell did he–

125
00:08:17.850 --> 00:08:20.940
While you were glued to
the transformations, dumbass!

126
00:08:20.940 --> 00:08:23.270
That bastard!

127
00:08:23.270 --> 00:08:25.900
I'll go find him
and take him down!

128
00:08:26.690 --> 00:08:29.240
Don't tell me he got
into the castle...

129
00:08:29.780 --> 00:08:31.370
If so, Nami...

130
00:08:33.580 --> 00:08:35.790
That son of a bitch!
If he lays a hand on Nami,

131
00:08:35.790 --> 00:08:37.370
I'll chop him into 100 pieces!
Hold it!

132
00:08:38.500 --> 00:08:42.290
Honestly, does he want to die?

133
00:08:45.500 --> 00:08:48.380
What the hell am I even looking at?!

134
00:08:48.380 --> 00:08:50.970
Is this really my Drum Castle?

135
00:08:52.760 --> 00:08:56.520
What have they done to it?

136
00:08:57.270 --> 00:09:00.520
They won't get away with this!

137
00:09:01.400 --> 00:09:05.020
I'll chew up every last one of them!

138
00:09:10.450 --> 00:09:12.990
This is no time to be resting in bed!

139
00:09:12.990 --> 00:09:15.370
I need to scram while
Doctorine is gone!

140
00:09:15.370 --> 00:09:17.790
I couldn't take being
stuck here for three days.

141
00:09:22.960 --> 00:09:25.460
How lucky! I can make
a clean getaway.

142
00:09:30.130 --> 00:09:32.180
Wh-Who's... this guy?!

143
00:09:32.180 --> 00:09:35.100
You must be one of the Straw Hats!

144
00:09:36.760 --> 00:09:38.770
He definitely looks like a bad guy!

145
00:09:40.100 --> 00:09:43.270
Nope, I think you've got me
mixed up with someone else!

146
00:09:43.270 --> 00:09:45.610
I have no clue what 
you're talking about!

147
00:09:46.020 --> 00:09:48.570
What?! I'm wrong?! Really?!

148
00:09:48.570 --> 00:09:52.280
Really! I'm just a navigator
who's passing through!

149
00:09:52.280 --> 00:09:53.700
Oh, I see...

150
00:09:53.700 --> 00:09:55.950
Well then, see ya!

151
00:09:55.950 --> 00:09:57.330
Okay!

152
00:10:00.750 --> 00:10:02.250
Liar!

153
00:10:03.460 --> 00:10:05.630
No!

154
00:10:04.080 --> 00:10:04.930
You hippo!

155
00:10:04.930 --> 00:10:06.540
Get back here!

156
00:10:05.630 --> 00:10:07.460
No!

157
00:10:08.300 --> 00:10:11.880
Don't come this way! Go away!

158
00:10:20.310 --> 00:10:22.310
Did I put on some weight recently?

159
00:10:22.730 --> 00:10:23.850
This calls for...

160
00:10:24.270 --> 00:10:25.730
Munch-Munch Factory!

161
00:10:26.480 --> 00:10:28.020
I'll eat myself!

162
00:10:33.700 --> 00:10:35.110
What's going on?!

163
00:10:46.710 --> 00:10:49.300
H-He turned into a bucket!

164
00:10:51.300 --> 00:10:55.590
Miraculous bone structure
shaping technique... complete!

165
00:11:01.100 --> 00:11:03.060
Slim Wapol!

166
00:11:04.850 --> 00:11:06.060
You won't get away.

167
00:11:06.650 --> 00:11:08.730
No!

168
00:11:14.820 --> 00:11:16.700
I'll eat you first!

169
00:11:17.530 --> 00:11:20.990
Found you!

170
00:11:29.380 --> 00:11:32.670
Huh? Was he always that skinny?

171
00:11:35.840 --> 00:11:37.300
Luffy...

172
00:11:37.300 --> 00:11:41.970
Care to explain what happened
to the jacket I lent you...?

173
00:11:42.930 --> 00:11:45.850
Do you know how much
this jacket cost?

174
00:11:45.850 --> 00:11:47.730
It was 28,800 belly!

175
00:11:47.730 --> 00:11:49.360
And that's after haggling!

176
00:11:49.360 --> 00:11:53.030
I'm sorry, but that guy
shot a bomb at me!

177
00:11:53.030 --> 00:11:55.360
There's nothing I could do!

178
00:11:56.240 --> 00:12:00.240
Seriously... But it's okay.
I forgive you.

179
00:12:00.240 --> 00:12:05.500
I didn't expect it to come back
in good shape when I let you borrow it.

180
00:12:05.500 --> 00:12:09.250
As compensation, you owe
triple its value plus interest.

181
00:12:09.250 --> 00:12:11.750
The total is 100,000 belly.
Consider it a loan.

182
00:12:12.670 --> 00:12:16.300
Hey, you knew this would happen!

183
00:12:18.680 --> 00:12:20.680
That's it, you filth!

184
00:12:21.550 --> 00:12:23.560
Man, he's sturdy!

185
00:12:25.350 --> 00:12:26.850
Look!

186
00:12:26.850 --> 00:12:29.100
Believe it or not, this is the armory!

187
00:12:29.100 --> 00:12:31.360
I'm the only one who has
the key to this room.

188
00:12:31.360 --> 00:12:35.530
Naturally, there's a vast array
of weapons inside.

189
00:12:35.530 --> 00:12:37.860
When I ingest all those weapons...

190
00:12:38.490 --> 00:12:41.780
and integrate them into my body
using Munch-Munch Shock,

191
00:12:41.780 --> 00:12:48.750
you'll witness a horrific
human weapon!

192
00:12:51.540 --> 00:12:54.550
Get ready! You'll soil yourselves
when this door opens!

193
00:12:54.550 --> 00:12:55.750
The key...

194
00:12:56.550 --> 00:12:58.590
is gone!

195
00:13:06.100 --> 00:13:07.520
This isn't over.

196
00:13:07.520 --> 00:13:10.520
Hey, he's running away! Wait!

197
00:13:11.730 --> 00:13:14.690
I've still got another trump card!

198
00:13:15.400 --> 00:13:18.190
Oh, it's just the key to the armory.

199
00:13:18.690 --> 00:13:21.820
It would've been nice if it were
the key to a treasure room.

200
00:13:21.820 --> 00:13:22.700
That's no fun...

201
00:13:22.690 --> 00:13:25.280
Nami my sweet!

202
00:13:25.280 --> 00:13:28.370
Thank goodness! You're safe!

203
00:13:29.160 --> 00:13:32.670
Why are you crawling, Sanji?
Are you all right?

204
00:13:33.040 --> 00:13:37.960
Oh Nami, are you really
that worried about me?!

205
00:13:37.960 --> 00:13:41.260
If I'm enveloped in that warmth...

206
00:13:41.760 --> 00:13:43.390
Quit it!

207
00:13:43.390 --> 00:13:45.260
Na... mi...

208
00:13:46.430 --> 00:13:50.430
Wait! Wait, wait!

209
00:13:50.850 --> 00:13:53.600
Dammit! The upper levels
are covered in snow, too!

210
00:13:53.980 --> 00:13:55.860
They'll all pay!

211
00:13:55.860 --> 00:13:59.570
I'll show them how great a king can be!

212
00:14:03.030 --> 00:14:06.410
The power of Drum is my power.

213
00:14:06.410 --> 00:14:08.700
I'll use Drum's ultimate weapon...

214
00:14:11.750 --> 00:14:16.750
the Royal Drum Tin-Pot Volley Gun!

215
00:14:21.300 --> 00:14:22.970
I've got you now! Get ready!

216
00:14:23.590 --> 00:14:25.930
I've got you, Straw Hat!

217
00:14:25.930 --> 00:14:27.390
Get blown to smithereens!

218
00:14:57.710 --> 00:14:59.550
A bird's nest...!

219
00:14:59.550 --> 00:15:01.050
Snow birds!

220
00:15:06.800 --> 00:15:10.100
How dare you make fun of me!

221
00:15:12.060 --> 00:15:13.520
Doctorine...

222
00:15:15.480 --> 00:15:17.690
He called me...

223
00:15:20.940 --> 00:15:22.690
his friend.

224
00:15:26.160 --> 00:15:29.660
I'm surprised to find a rope
connected to the castle here...

225
00:15:29.660 --> 00:15:32.080
A young man from town
discovered it by chance.

226
00:15:32.080 --> 00:15:36.170
This place used to be
Dr. Kureha's house!

227
00:15:41.420 --> 00:15:43.170
What a great view!

228
00:15:43.170 --> 00:15:46.050
Yeah, but isn't this
a little overcrowded?

229
00:15:46.050 --> 00:15:48.300
We can't let Dalton
go alone like this!

230
00:15:48.300 --> 00:15:49.720
We'll fight, too!

231
00:15:49.720 --> 00:15:53.180
W-Well, I suppose so,
but we'll never get there at this rate!

232
00:15:57.440 --> 00:15:59.810
Peddle! Peddle faster!

233
00:15:59.810 --> 00:16:01.730
Dalton, don't push yourself.

234
00:16:02.520 --> 00:16:04.030
Wapol...

235
00:16:04.030 --> 00:16:06.740
Who do you think you are, Dalton?

236
00:16:08.360 --> 00:16:11.830
"No amount of medicine
can cure a fool" you say...?

237
00:16:13.240 --> 00:16:15.750
Who are you calling a fool?

238
00:16:16.460 --> 00:16:21.040
You think you've become
the people's champion of justice?!

239
00:16:21.040 --> 00:16:23.300
Get over yourself!
You're merely a vassal!

240
00:16:26.090 --> 00:16:31.720
A week or so in this cell should
make you realize your mistake.

241
00:16:31.720 --> 00:16:36.520
I imagine your impulsive rebellion
will have subsided by then.

242
00:16:39.560 --> 00:16:43.440
You're an excellent guard,
trusted by the citizens.

243
00:16:43.440 --> 00:16:45.570
Reconsider it, Dalton.

244
00:16:48.240 --> 00:16:52.660
You got caught up in a childish fantasy,
all thanks to that quack doctor Hiriluk!

245
00:16:52.660 --> 00:16:56.580
What good will abdicating your status
and destroying the country do you?!

246
00:16:56.580 --> 00:16:59.330
I'll forgive you, Dalton

247
00:16:59.330 --> 00:17:02.380
but only if you say...

248
00:17:04.340 --> 00:17:09.680
"I'm sorry" to me, the king.

249
00:17:14.930 --> 00:17:16.270
To hell with status!

250
00:17:16.270 --> 00:17:18.770
To hell with the king!

251
00:17:21.350 --> 00:17:22.980
I'm the king!

252
00:17:22.980 --> 00:17:26.190
I'm the king of the Kingdom
of Drum! I'm the ki–

253
00:17:29.110 --> 00:17:29.950
It's over.

254
00:17:31.320 --> 00:17:33.160
It doesn't matter...

255
00:17:33.160 --> 00:17:35.870
if you're a king or a god.

256
00:17:36.200 --> 00:17:39.790
I don't care if you're some big shot!

257
00:17:40.460 --> 00:17:42.330
After all, I'm a pirate.

258
00:17:44.170 --> 00:17:46.550
You should care, Straw Hat!

259
00:17:46.550 --> 00:17:50.130
The Kingdom of Drum is a member
of the World Government.

260
00:17:50.630 --> 00:17:54.970
Listen, this is a world-class offense!

261
00:17:54.970 --> 00:17:57.850
Like I said, that doesn't matter, either!

262
00:17:57.850 --> 00:18:00.100
This is my own fight!

263
00:18:01.600 --> 00:18:04.060
Y-You damn straw idiot...!

264
00:18:04.060 --> 00:18:05.520
I'll digest you!

265
00:18:08.360 --> 00:18:09.110
Just try!

266
00:18:09.780 --> 00:18:10.860
Not yet!

267
00:18:10.860 --> 00:18:13.740
Munch-Munch Shock:
Tongue Cannon!

268
00:18:13.740 --> 00:18:16.030
Whoa! His tongue became a cannon!

269
00:18:16.030 --> 00:18:17.330
Disappear!

270
00:18:34.890 --> 00:18:37.930
Dalton! Please hang in there!

271
00:18:37.930 --> 00:18:39.350
What should we do?

272
00:18:39.770 --> 00:18:42.600
Dalton! Dalton!

273
00:18:42.600 --> 00:18:44.940
Dalton!

274
00:18:45.270 --> 00:18:47.690
I'm... I'm alright.

275
00:18:51.440 --> 00:18:52.900
Dalton...

276
00:18:57.620 --> 00:18:59.280
I'll make sure...

277
00:18:59.280 --> 00:19:02.000
to put an end to his tyranny!

278
00:19:02.000 --> 00:19:04.710
To hell with history!

279
00:19:05.750 --> 00:19:08.630
C'mon, get a grip, Dalton.

280
00:19:08.630 --> 00:19:13.090
You think governance is
about caring... for your country?

281
00:19:14.220 --> 00:19:16.130
A government doesn't need a heart.

282
00:19:16.510 --> 00:19:17.760
He's right.

283
00:19:17.760 --> 00:19:19.470
What's important is the system.

284
00:19:26.190 --> 00:19:28.190
Wh-What are you doing?!

285
00:19:29.980 --> 00:19:31.820
Let me go! Stop it!

286
00:19:31.820 --> 00:19:35.240
I still have a lot of patients to treat!

287
00:19:35.240 --> 00:19:37.110
Throw him into the sea!

288
00:19:37.110 --> 00:19:38.950
If he resists, kill him.

289
00:19:39.490 --> 00:19:41.830
Hey, let me go! Please!

290
00:19:41.830 --> 00:19:44.910
My patients are
waiting for me! Please!

291
00:19:47.420 --> 00:19:49.880
To hell with this regime!

292
00:19:54.340 --> 00:19:56.340
Good...

293
00:19:56.340 --> 00:19:58.890
So none of them are sick?

294
00:20:01.050 --> 00:20:03.640
What's wrong with wanting
a country to have a heart?!

295
00:20:10.810 --> 00:20:13.190
D-Dalton! What are you...?!

296
00:20:11.730 --> 00:20:12.690
Dalton...!

297
00:20:15.740 --> 00:20:17.610
Dynamite!

298
00:20:17.610 --> 00:20:19.280
Listen, everyone.

299
00:20:19.280 --> 00:20:22.700
Once we get to the castle
and I'm inside, get down.

300
00:20:28.290 --> 00:20:30.580
What a hippo! He got too cocky!

301
00:20:33.670 --> 00:20:35.380
Actually, that's you.

302
00:20:34.840 --> 00:20:36.090
Wh-What?!

303
00:20:35.380 --> 00:20:38.050
One, two...

304
00:20:38.050 --> 00:20:39.890
What?! What are you going to do?!

305
00:20:41.050 --> 00:20:41.930
Hey, let me go!

306
00:20:41.930 --> 00:20:45.310
Gum-Gum...

307
00:20:45.810 --> 00:20:48.100
Crossbow!

308
00:21:03.780 --> 00:21:05.290
Doctorine...

309
00:21:05.290 --> 00:21:06.290
Yeah...

310
00:21:06.910 --> 00:21:10.620
Looks like... his time has finally come...

311
00:21:15.380 --> 00:21:19.300
Don't mess with someone's flag
if you can't back it up!

312
00:21:19.300 --> 00:21:22.300
Gum-Gum...

313
00:21:22.890 --> 00:21:23.970
Doctor...

314
00:21:25.850 --> 00:21:27.390
Hold on a sec!

315
00:21:25.930 --> 00:21:29.270
Gum-Gum-Gum-Gum-Gum-Gum...

316
00:21:27.390 --> 00:21:29.270
I'll give you status and a medal!

317
00:21:29.730 --> 00:21:32.980
Look! There's someone
on top of the castle!

318
00:21:38.650 --> 00:21:39.820
Doctor...

319
00:21:44.490 --> 00:21:46.410
The Kingdom...

320
00:21:47.540 --> 00:21:49.500
The Kingdom of Drum...

321
00:21:53.830 --> 00:21:56.340
Fine... I'll make you vice king!

322
00:21:57.170 --> 00:21:59.260
...is about to fall!

323
00:21:59.260 --> 00:22:03.550
Bazooka!

324
00:22:29.080 --> 00:22:33.290
The Kingdom of Drum was defeated
by the skull and crossbones.

325
00:22:49.390 --> 00:22:51.390
Alright! I'll go scout ahead!

326
00:22:51.390 --> 00:22:52.320
Don't worry.

327
00:22:52.320 --> 00:22:54.560
You can follow once it's clear.

328
00:22:55.270 --> 00:22:58.150
Zoro's going ahead of me again!
Serious power, activate!

329
00:23:10.370 --> 00:23:11.910
Hey, quit pulling!

330
00:23:11.910 --> 00:23:13.370
Alright! I got your back.

331
00:23:13.370 --> 00:23:16.420
If you're that scared,
just wait behind for now!

332
00:23:17.380 --> 00:23:20.210
I-I-I'm n-n-not s-s-scared...!

333
00:23:20.210 --> 00:23:22.380
B-Because I'm...

334
00:23:22.380 --> 00:23:24.420
What the hell?!

335
00:23:23.760 --> 00:23:24.420
Luffy!

336
00:23:25.550 --> 00:23:27.090
Zoro?! Usopp?!

337
00:23:39.690 --> 00:23:41.820
What'd you do that for, asshole?!

338
00:23:41.820 --> 00:23:43.650
Oh, it's you guys!

339
00:23:45.400 --> 00:23:47.990
Those looked like
the bad guys' clothes,

340
00:23:47.990 --> 00:23:50.200
so I thought you were them!

341
00:23:50.700 --> 00:23:52.830
I guess you guys climbed up, too.

342
00:23:52.830 --> 00:23:56.580
Usopp, didn't you say
you couldn't make it?

343
00:23:57.830 --> 00:23:58.670
That's absurd!

344
00:23:59.290 --> 00:24:02.550
If I see a mountain in front of me,
I climb it. I'm that kind of guy.

345
00:24:02.550 --> 00:24:06.130
But arriving on this precipice
was quite an adventure.

346
00:24:06.550 --> 00:24:08.260
We came up by ropeway.

347
00:24:08.260 --> 00:24:11.600
Luffy, are Nami and Sanji okay?

348
00:24:12.010 --> 00:24:14.100
Yep, they're all better.

349
00:24:12.220 --> 00:24:14.100
Now, get it together...

350
00:24:15.020 --> 00:24:16.560
I'm glad to hear that!

351
00:24:15.020 --> 00:24:17.940
We were also attacked by
a huge condor on our way!

352
00:24:17.940 --> 00:24:19.520
Man, was I surprised.

353
00:24:19.900 --> 00:24:22.730
But then I was like—
or maybe I should say—

354
00:24:20.650 --> 00:24:22.230
I'm glad...

355
00:24:23.070 --> 00:24:25.320
it's just what you'd expect from me!

356
00:24:24.860 --> 00:24:28.360
So, what were you doing
on top of the castle?

357
00:24:25.320 --> 00:24:28.360
The moment it dove for my heart,

358
00:24:29.240 --> 00:24:35.000
Captain Me twirled gracefully out of
harm's way and mounted the condor!

359
00:24:29.910 --> 00:24:32.280
I was beating the crap out of the king.

360
00:24:34.160 --> 00:24:37.620
Just as I thought, the one soaring
into the sky was Wapol!

361
00:24:35.000 --> 00:24:37.620
It was really me!

362
00:24:37.620 --> 00:24:40.880
I put a rope around its neck and said,

363
00:24:38.080 --> 00:24:39.170
You beat him?!

364
00:24:39.500 --> 00:24:40.880
Yep! Why?

365
00:24:40.880 --> 00:24:43.590
"My name is Captain Usopp!"

366
00:24:43.590 --> 00:24:45.920
But what about his two top officers?

367
00:24:46.420 --> 00:24:48.010
The reindeer beat them up.

368
00:24:48.630 --> 00:24:50.890
The reindeer... beat those two...?

369
00:24:50.890 --> 00:24:55.560
How's that? Are you guys amazed?
Check me out!

370
00:24:52.100 --> 00:24:57.140
Oh yeah! Usopp, listen!
I found a new crewmate!

371
00:24:58.390 --> 00:24:59.230
What?

372
00:25:00.020 --> 00:25:01.900
Reindeer...

373
00:25:11.610 --> 00:25:13.070
A blue nose...

374
00:25:15.080 --> 00:25:16.580
Wait!

375
00:25:17.040 --> 00:25:20.040
I apologize on behalf of all those
who laughed at Hiriluk's death,

376
00:25:21.790 --> 00:25:26.000
but you'll needlessly join him
if you fight them in this state.

377
00:25:27.800 --> 00:25:33.430
This country has seen
enough sacrifices for one day.

378
00:25:35.680 --> 00:25:38.270
You're that reindeer...

379
00:25:38.890 --> 00:25:44.230
I see... You've been fighting
for us since back then!

380
00:25:51.320 --> 00:25:52.530
Thank you.

381
00:25:53.410 --> 00:25:54.620
Drum will...

382
00:25:55.910 --> 00:25:58.240
definitely be reborn...!

383
00:26:08.210 --> 00:26:11.170
Wh-What's that strange creature?!

384
00:26:11.170 --> 00:26:12.840
A-A reindeer?

385
00:26:12.840 --> 00:26:15.350
No... That's...

386
00:26:15.350 --> 00:26:17.260
a m-m-m-monst–

387
00:26:17.260 --> 00:26:18.430
Hey, stop it!

388
00:26:19.810 --> 00:26:21.390
It's a monster!

389
00:26:21.850 --> 00:26:22.980
It's a monster!

390
00:26:22.980 --> 00:26:25.360
It's a monster!

391
00:26:27.020 --> 00:26:28.900
Don't call him a monster!

392
00:26:28.900 --> 00:26:31.110
He's the new crewmate
I was talking about!

393
00:26:31.110 --> 00:26:32.400
What?! That thing is?!

394
00:26:32.400 --> 00:26:35.160
He got shocked and ran away!

395
00:26:36.410 --> 00:26:38.990
Wait! Monster!

396
00:26:38.990 --> 00:26:40.200
– Hey!
– Hey!

397
00:26:40.200 --> 00:26:42.830
Hey! Reindeer!

398
00:26:43.750 --> 00:26:45.790
Hey, wait!

399
00:26:45.790 --> 00:26:47.920
Hey! Reindeer!

400
00:26:48.750 --> 00:26:51.340
You're my friend!

401
00:26:51.340 --> 00:26:54.050
Hey! Reindeer!

402
00:26:54.050 --> 00:26:57.140
You're definitely our new crewmate!

403
00:26:55.890 --> 00:26:57.140
Doctor...

404
00:26:57.140 --> 00:26:59.100
Hey!

405
00:26:57.760 --> 00:26:59.100
This is for the best, right?

406
00:26:59.850 --> 00:27:01.720
Wait!

407
00:26:59.850 --> 00:27:01.100
This is...

408
00:27:01.720 --> 00:27:03.850
Wait! Reindeer!

409
00:27:03.850 --> 00:27:06.440
There's no way I'm waiting!

410
00:27:12.190 --> 00:27:14.070
Are you all right, Dalton?!

411
00:27:14.070 --> 00:27:15.700
Yes, I am well.

412
00:27:15.700 --> 00:27:17.990
I just feel a little drained, is all.

413
00:27:17.990 --> 00:27:20.240
Hey, you guys!

414
00:27:21.620 --> 00:27:24.330
– D-Dr. Kureha!
– D-Dr. Kureha!

415
00:27:26.710 --> 00:27:29.090
Are ya happy, brats?

416
00:27:29.090 --> 00:27:31.550
Take that injured guy
to the medical ward.

417
00:27:32.300 --> 00:27:35.680
Nami, you should really
finish your medical treatment.

418
00:27:35.680 --> 00:27:36.800
Be quiet!

419
00:27:36.800 --> 00:27:41.010
If I don't escape now, our departure for
Alabasta will be delayed by two days!

420
00:27:41.010 --> 00:27:44.100
Do you wanna keep
seeing Vivi suffer?!

421
00:27:44.100 --> 00:27:46.480
Quit your grumbling, you two,

422
00:27:46.480 --> 00:27:50.110
and get back to the medical ward!

423
00:28:07.750 --> 00:28:11.840
As I thought, his injuries have gotten
worse since he overexerted himself.

424
00:28:16.090 --> 00:28:17.630
Now...

425
00:28:18.010 --> 00:28:19.260
Dalton.

426
00:28:19.260 --> 00:28:23.680
Where's the key to the armory?
You know where it is, don't you?

427
00:28:24.810 --> 00:28:27.850
The key to the armory...
Why do you need such a thing?

428
00:28:27.850 --> 00:28:30.730
It's none of your business.

429
00:28:30.730 --> 00:28:34.440
That key... Wapol always
kept it on his person.

430
00:28:34.440 --> 00:28:37.320
If that's still the case,
it flew off with him...

431
00:28:37.320 --> 00:28:39.030
What?! Is that right?

432
00:28:39.030 --> 00:28:40.320
Well, crap...

433
00:28:40.320 --> 00:28:42.200
Doctorine...

434
00:28:43.080 --> 00:28:46.580
About the treatment fee for our crew,
would you make it all free?

435
00:28:46.580 --> 00:28:50.630
Also, would you
discharge me right away?

436
00:28:50.630 --> 00:28:54.630
Did you ask the impossible
just for the heck of it?

437
00:28:54.630 --> 00:28:58.590
As my fee, I'll take all the money
and cargo on your ship,

438
00:28:59.050 --> 00:29:02.470
and you'll stay here and rest
for at least two more days!

439
00:29:03.010 --> 00:29:04.430
Nami, she's right!

440
00:29:04.430 --> 00:29:06.310
You should finish your treatment!

441
00:29:06.310 --> 00:29:09.140
I'll be fine! It's not like
I'm dying anymore!

442
00:29:09.140 --> 00:29:11.560
That's not a good reason!

443
00:29:15.570 --> 00:29:19.950
You need the key
to the armory, right?

444
00:29:19.950 --> 00:29:21.070
What?!

445
00:29:21.070 --> 00:29:22.780
Why do you have that key?!

446
00:29:22.780 --> 00:29:24.530
Is that the real one?

447
00:29:24.530 --> 00:29:25.990
How'd you get it?!

448
00:29:25.990 --> 00:29:27.290
I stole it.

449
00:29:27.790 --> 00:29:31.620
You've got guts dictating
terms to me like that.

450
00:29:31.620 --> 00:29:34.750
You're quite the precocious girl.

451
00:29:35.800 --> 00:29:37.050
Alright, fine.

452
00:29:37.510 --> 00:29:41.010
You don't have to pay
my fee, but that's all.

453
00:29:41.470 --> 00:29:44.970
As a doctor, I can't
accept the other term.

454
00:29:44.970 --> 00:29:46.310
Wait a sec!

455
00:29:46.310 --> 00:29:48.810
In that case, the deal's off!
Give it back!

456
00:29:50.100 --> 00:29:51.480
Listen, girl.

457
00:29:52.270 --> 00:29:55.610
I have to leave this room
to take care of some things.

458
00:29:55.610 --> 00:29:59.110
There's a wardrobe with
my coat in the back room.

459
00:29:59.110 --> 00:30:02.160
And it's not like I'm posting guards...

460
00:30:02.160 --> 00:30:06.490
Additionally, that young man's
backbone treatment is complete.

461
00:30:06.490 --> 00:30:09.410
But listen! Don't you dare run off!

462
00:30:09.910 --> 00:30:12.790
You guys, come with me.
I need you for heavy lifting.

463
00:30:12.790 --> 00:30:14.210
– Yes, ma'am!
– Yes, ma'am!

464
00:30:21.800 --> 00:30:25.890
"Take my coat, grab Sanji,
and escape while I'm gone."

465
00:30:25.890 --> 00:30:29.020
Yeah... that's how
it sounded to me, too.

466
00:30:39.730 --> 00:30:41.860
I sure ran around a lot.

467
00:30:41.860 --> 00:30:43.820
It's nighttime already...

468
00:30:44.360 --> 00:30:46.570
I don't hear their voices anymore...

469
00:30:46.570 --> 00:30:49.330
Looks like they're gone.

470
00:30:49.910 --> 00:30:51.910
This is for the best...

471
00:30:51.910 --> 00:30:54.290
I can't leave this place.

472
00:30:56.000 --> 00:30:57.840
It's a full moon tonight...

473
00:30:59.000 --> 00:31:02.760
Hey! Reindeer!

474
00:31:02.760 --> 00:31:06.720
Let's be pirates together!

475
00:31:03.470 --> 00:31:06.720
I can't believe they're still looking for me!

476
00:31:06.720 --> 00:31:09.850
Hey, Luffy. Just give it up already.

477
00:31:09.850 --> 00:31:12.850
We've been looking for hours
with no sign of him.

478
00:31:12.850 --> 00:31:16.230
He doesn't wanna be a pirate.

479
00:31:16.230 --> 00:31:17.860
That's not true!

480
00:31:17.860 --> 00:31:19.980
I wanna take him with us!

481
00:31:19.980 --> 00:31:23.070
Like I said, that's what
you want, right?!

482
00:31:23.740 --> 00:31:26.070
It's not that I don't wanna go...

483
00:31:26.070 --> 00:31:27.950
Reindeer!

484
00:31:28.320 --> 00:31:31.790
Come out, reindeer!

485
00:31:31.790 --> 00:31:33.120
But I won't go!

486
00:31:33.120 --> 00:31:34.410
I can't go!

487
00:31:34.750 --> 00:31:36.870
I'm not like those guys!

488
00:31:44.470 --> 00:31:46.090
Reindeer!

489
00:31:50.140 --> 00:31:51.140
Tony!

490
00:31:54.480 --> 00:31:58.560
Hey, let's be pirates together! Okay?!

491
00:31:59.400 --> 00:32:00.480
It's impossible.

492
00:32:00.480 --> 00:32:03.360
How could it be impossible
when it's so fun?!

493
00:32:03.360 --> 00:32:04.940
Hey, that doesn't make sense!

494
00:32:06.400 --> 00:32:07.780
But...

495
00:32:10.530 --> 00:32:12.450
But I'm a reindeer!

496
00:32:12.450 --> 00:32:15.160
I have antlers and hooves...!

497
00:32:16.250 --> 00:32:17.870
I even have a blue nose!

498
00:32:19.330 --> 00:32:23.170
Can you guys heal
the scar in his heart?

499
00:32:25.300 --> 00:32:28.800
It's true... I wanna be
a pirate, but...

500
00:32:31.390 --> 00:32:33.640
I'm not even a human!

501
00:32:33.640 --> 00:32:35.220
I'm a monster!

502
00:32:35.220 --> 00:32:38.230
I can't join your crew!

503
00:32:38.230 --> 00:32:39.270
So...

504
00:32:40.480 --> 00:32:42.230
So I just came to say thank you...

505
00:32:45.490 --> 00:32:47.740
I really appreciate you guys.

506
00:32:48.400 --> 00:32:50.200
Thank you for asking me to join you.

507
00:32:55.120 --> 00:32:57.160
I'll stay here, but...

508
00:33:00.370 --> 00:33:03.090
one day, if you feel like it,
stop by agai–

509
00:33:03.090 --> 00:33:04.050
Shut up!

510
00:33:04.050 --> 00:33:07.050
Let's go!

511
00:33:18.640 --> 00:33:21.190
Is “shut up” supposed
to be welcoming?
